127int EVP_MD_CTX_copy_ex(EVP_MD_CTX *out, const EVP_MD_CTX *in) {
128 // |in->digest| may be NULL if this is a signing |EVP_MD_CTX| for, e.g.,
129 // Ed25519 which does not hash with |EVP_MD_CTX|.
130 if (in == NULL || (in->pctx == NULL && in->digest == NULL)) {
131 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, DIGEST_R_INPUT_NOT_INITIALIZED);
132 return 0;
133 }
134
135 EVP_PKEY_CTX *pctx = NULL;
136 assert(in->pctx == NULL || in->pctx_ops != NULL);
137 if (in->pctx) {
138 pctx = in->pctx_ops->dup(in->pctx);
139 if (!pctx) {
140 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
141 return 0;
142 }
143 }
144
145 uint8_t *tmp_buf = NULL;
146 if (in->digest != NULL) {
147 if (out->digest != in->digest) {
148 assert(in->digest->ctx_size != 0);
149 tmp_buf = OPENSSL_malloc(in->digest->ctx_size);
150 if (tmp_buf == NULL) {
151 if (pctx) {
152 in->pctx_ops->free(pctx);
153 }
154 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
155 return 0;
156 }
157 } else {
158 // |md_data| will be the correct size in this case. It's removed from
159 // |out| so that |EVP_MD_CTX_cleanup| doesn't free it, and then it's
160 // reused.
161 tmp_buf = out->md_data;
162 out->md_data = NULL;
163 }
164 }
165
166 EVP_MD_CTX_cleanup(out);
167
168 out->digest = in->digest;
169 out->md_data = tmp_buf;
170 if (in->digest != NULL) {
171 OPENSSL_memcpy(out->md_data, in->md_data, in->digest->ctx_size);
172 }
173 out->pctx = pctx;
174 out->pctx_ops = in->pctx_ops;
175 assert(out->pctx == NULL || out->pctx_ops != NULL);
176
177 return 1;
178}

191int EVP_DigestInit_ex(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, const EVP_MD *type, ENGINE *engine) {
192 if (ctx->digest != type) {
193 assert(type->ctx_size != 0);
194 uint8_t *md_data = OPENSSL_malloc(type->ctx_size);
195 if (md_data == NULL) {
196 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(DIGEST, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
197 return 0;
198 }
199
200 OPENSSL_free(ctx->md_data);
201 ctx->md_data = md_data;
202 ctx->digest = type;
203 }
204
205 assert(ctx->pctx == NULL || ctx->pctx_ops != NULL);
206
207 ctx->digest->init(ctx);
208 return 1;
209}

237int EVP_Digest(const void *data, size_t count, uint8_t *out_md,
238 unsigned int *out_size, const EVP_MD *type, ENGINE *impl) {
239 EVP_MD_CTX ctx;
240 int ret;
241
242 EVP_MD_CTX_init(&ctx);
243 ret = EVP_DigestInit_ex(&ctx, type, impl) &&
244 EVP_DigestUpdate(&ctx, data, count) &&
245 EVP_DigestFinal_ex(&ctx, out_md, out_size);
246 EVP_MD_CTX_cleanup(&ctx);
247
248 return ret;
249}
